<h3 id="image-galleries">Image galleries</h3>

<p>Here‚Äôs a really neat custom feature we added ‚Äì galleries:</p>

<div class="gallery" data-columns="3">
	<img src="/images/demo/demo-portrait.jpg" />
	<img src="/images/demo/demo-landscape.jpg" />
	<img src="/images/demo/demo-square.jpg" />
	<img src="/images/demo/demo-landscape-2.jpg" />
</div>

<p>Inspired by the Galleries feature from WordPress, we‚Äôve made it easy to create grid layouts for your images. Just use a bit of simple HTML in your post to create a masonry grid image layout:</p>

<div class="language-html highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="nt">&lt;div</span> <span class="na">class=</span><span class="s">"gallery"</span> <span class="na">data-columns=</span><span class="s">"3"</span><span class="nt">&gt;</span>
    <span class="nt">&lt;img</span> <span class="na">src=</span><span class="s">"/images/demo/demo-portrait.jpg"</span><span class="nt">&gt;</span>
    <span class="nt">&lt;img</span> <span class="na">src=</span><span class="s">"/images/demo/demo-landscape.jpg"</span><span class="nt">&gt;</span>
    <span class="nt">&lt;img</span> <span class="na">src=</span><span class="s">"/images/demo/demo-square.jpg"</span><span class="nt">&gt;</span>
    <span class="nt">&lt;img</span> <span class="na">src=</span><span class="s">"/images/demo/demo-landscape-2.jpg"</span><span class="nt">&gt;</span>
<span class="nt">&lt;/div&gt;</span>
</code></pre></div></div>

<p><em>See what we did there? Code and syntax highlighting is built-in too!</em></p>

<p>Change the number inside the ‚Äòcolumns‚Äô setting to create different types of gallery for all kinds of purposes. You can even click on each image to seamlessly enlarge it on the page.</p>

<hr />

<h3 id="image-carousels">Image carousels</h3>

<p>Here‚Äôs another gallery with only one column, which creates a carousel slide-show instead.</p>

<p>A nice little feature: the carousel only advances when it is in view, so your visitors won‚Äôt scroll down to find it half way through your images.</p>

<div class="gallery" data-columns="1">
	<img src="/images/demo/demo-landscape.jpg" />
	<img src="/images/demo/demo-landscape-2.jpg" />
</div>

<h3 id="what-about-videos">What about videos?</h3>

<p>Videos are an awesome way to show off your work in a more engaging and personal way, and we‚Äôve made sure they work great on our themes. Just paste an embed code from YouTube or Vimeo, and the theme makes sure it displays perfectly:</p>

<iframe src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/19536258?color=ffffff&amp;title=0&amp;byline=0&amp;portrait=0" width="640" height="360" frameborder="0" webkitallowfullscreen="" mozallowfullscreen="" allowfullscreen=""></iframe>

